request.description:
Opens SSE stream for live ASR transcription. Holds slot 0 for the entire recording session.

Expected: 200 with Content-Type: text/event-stream. Slot 0 occupied.
SSE events: data: {"token":"Hello","index":0,"done":false}

Poll slot state after a batch NMT request completes (simulated by waiting for batch response). Verifies slot count dropped from 4/4.

Expected: { slots: { total: 4, in_use: 3, available: 1 }, state: 'DISPATCHING' }
Dispatch loop fires within <0.15ms of slot release.

Validate SSE token event format. Each token must conform to the documented schema.

Expected token events:
  data: {"token":"Hello","index":0,"done":false}
  data: {"token":" world","index":1,"done":false}
  data: {"token":"","index":2,"done":true}

Final event:
  data: {"event":"stream:done","total_tokens":3,"duration_ms":150}

Forwarding latency: < 0.01ms (AsyncGenerator yield, no buffering).
